    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for a Medium model risk, Medium model influence, Medium decision consequence context. The single shortfall in Test conditions (achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is mitigated by the worst-case loading argument documented in the factor rationale and does not invalidate the overall credibility of the FEA evidence. All quantitative acceptance criteria for output comparison are satisfied across both laboratories. The assessment team accepts the FEA evidence as adequate to support the 510(k) submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design.",
